          "distinct": true,
          "id": "750d5fc6a9ccebb00662416e952546713a9a5d16",
          "message": "Updates renamer (#172)\n\nSome improvements to the tree renamer:\n\n- [x] Adds makefile target, `make list-trees` that uses rgrep and find,\ntogether with awk to list all the trees in the project.\n- [x] Updates the Python script to use this utility rather than calling\n`forester` to get a list of trees.\n - [x] Add a makefile target for renaming trees (#171):\n   - Checks that there are no duplicate trees\n   - Checks that the repo is synchronised with upstream/main\n   - Checks that the repo is in a clean state\n   - Displays the ouput a dry run, and asks for confirmation\n   - Then performs the renaming\n   - Optionally makes a git commit - enabled by default\n- [x] Add some contributor documentation for how to name trees and use\nthe renamer etc.\n\nThis partially (or maybe completely?) addresses #113:\n\n> The tree ID renamer script suffers from a series of issues which makes\nit impractical to work with, and that may be improved.\n\n\n> - Forester build dependency. Currently the script uses the build\nartifacts of forester, which is not great for multiple reasons:\n> 1. It requires that `forester` is installed, which we ultimately don't\nwant. [Get rid of user-side `forester` dependency\n#114](https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/issues/114)\n> 2. It requires that the project is built before the script can run,\nadding an extra step to the process of renaming IDs.\n>       3. This solution is fragile wrt. dirty repo states.\n\nI think this change fixes all of these issues, `forester` is no longer a\ndependency of the tree renamer, and the forest does not need to be build\n- or even buildable for this to work.\n\n\n> - Python dependency. It might be possible to implement the same\nfunctionality with `sed` (which ships with unix based systems (TODO:\nalso document alternative for windows users(WSL?)))\n\nThe Python dependency is still there. Maybe when I have time I can try\nand port the whole thing to bash, but since we have a dependency on\nPython now via `pre-commit` I don't think this is a top priority.\n\n> - Every subtree must be manually ID'd. An alternative we've discussed\nis to autofill unID'd subtrees of the form `\\subtree[]{` with the script\n(note the empty `[...]`).\n\nThis is still an issue; however I think this could be solved by having\ntooling to automatically generate a new unique random ID in the editor\nfor example. I don't think the proposed solution (of having blank\nsubtrees) is ideal since we still want to be able to reference the\nsubtrees before the final renaming.\n\n> - There seems to be performance issues with the current implementation\nwhere it takes multiple minutes to run.\n\nWhilst I never encountered this with the last system - I suspect it was\ncaused by forester itself having to build the forest before being able\nto generate the forest JSON data. This new system circumvents forester\nso this shouldn't be an issue.",
          "timestamp": "2026-06-04T14:18:50Z",
          "tree_id": "d8918be175d07879893a39c370fc96fe105a6abc",
